    <h2>5 Facts About Sir David Attenborough</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>David Frederick Attenborough was born in England on May 8th, 1926. He is the middle of three long-lived sons whom was an actor and an executive, respectively.</li>
     
      <li>As a child, he spent his childhood collecting stones, fossils as well as natural specimens.</li>
      
      <li>Attenborough had attended a life changing lecture that was held in 1963. The famous conservationist Archibald Belaney (a.k.a Grey Owk) talked about the importance of saving the environment. That meeting inspired Attenborough's growing passion for flora and fauna, as well as for the need for environmental awareness.</li>
      
      <li>While he was being educated at Wyggeston Grammar School for Boys in Leicester, he had won a shcolarship to Clare College, Cambrige in 1945, where he studied geology and zoology and obtained a degree in natural sciences.</li>
      
      <li>1947 was the year he was called up for national service in the Royal Navy and spent two years stationed in North Wales and the Firth of Forth.</li>
    </ol>
    
